sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for the bright yellow fluorescent protein SYFP2. SYFP2 is a GFP based monomeric protein with a narrow fluorescence emission spectrum with a maximum at 515 nm. Bacteria expressing SYFP2 are reported to be 12 times brighter than those expressing EYFP(Q69K) and almost 2-fold brighter than bacteria expressing Venus (Ref. 10.1021/bi0516273). Codon optimized for expression in E coli by DNA 2.0. Mutations compared to wtGFP amino acid sequence (GenBank Accession number M62653) are F46L F64L S65G S72A M153T V163A S175G T203Y A206K.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Amino acid sequence taken from the article by Kremers et al 2006.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: DNA 2.0 have created a large set of new colored and fluorescent proteins by back-translating a set of sequences from Genbank, using their proprietary GeneDesigner software. To create these proteins, they simultaneously minimized sequence differences and and derived an E. coli codon bias for high protein expression. Gene fragments were designed to create chimeric genes when pooled. A subset of the resultant chimeras were selected as base genes from which multiple iterations of libraries with targeted substitutions were made. (from DNA 2.0)

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: mRFP (DsRed) derived, altered to be a biobrick by removing a PstI site and adding in the ends.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Made a point mutation to eliminate a PstI site in the middle and then added BioBrick ends using PCR.

Sequenced using primers that bind to the pSB1A2 plasmid on either side of the brick.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: mCherry from Roger Y. Tsien's lab, altered to be BioBrick compatible

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The sequence has been codon optimized for expression in E coli by DNA 2.0.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for the bright blue fluorescent protein mTagBFP. mTagBFP is a monomeric protein with a narrow fluorescence emission spectrum with a maximum at 456 nm. It has a tyrosine-based chromophore, giving it substantially higher brightness, faster chromophore maturation and higher pH stability than blue fluorescent proteins with a histidine in the chromophore. Subach et. al. started with a red fluorescent protein (TagRed) and converted it to a bright blue monomeric protein. See the article listed in source. The sequence has been codon optimized for expression in E coli by DNA 2.0.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Subach, O. M., I. S. Gundorov, et al. (2008). "Conversion of red fluorescent protein into a bright blue probe." Chem Biol 15(10): 1116-24.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erik Gullberg
